first thing in the morning.

520
00:32:51.010 --> 00:32:52.595
It's right here on the box.

521
00:32:52.678 --> 00:32:54.388
Okay.

522
00:32:56.599 --> 00:32:57.808
Little Carter in here?

523
00:32:57.892 --> 00:32:59.351
I haven't seen him.

524
00:33:00.728 --> 00:33:02.771
Thank you. Lloyd.

525
00:33:19.163 --> 00:33:20.789
You don't waste any time.

526
00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:24.752
It ain't the kind of thing
you want laying around.

527
00:33:27.004 --> 00:33:28.172
Where'd you bury it?

528
00:33:28.255 --> 00:33:30.007
We didn't bury it.

529
00:33:30.090 --> 00:33:31.759
That one feeds the wolves.

530
00:33:34.887 --> 00:33:35.888
No Carter?

531
00:33:36.305 --> 00:33:37.806
Tack room.

532
00:33:41.435 --> 00:33:42.686
Thanks.

533
00:33:46.899 --> 00:33:48.817
(KNOCKING)

534
00:33:53.656 --> 00:33:54.698
(DOOR CLOSES)

535
00:33:59.954 --> 00:34:02.665
I fell in love in this room.

536
00:34:11.632 --> 00:34:13.676
I got pregnant in this room.

537
00:34:18.138 --> 00:34:20.558
And then I told the love of my life...

538
00:34:21.517 --> 00:34:24.019
that I never wanted to see him again.

539
00:34:25.563 --> 00:34:27.815
He was sat right where you are.

540
00:34:31.652 --> 00:34:33.445
Why'd you do that?

541
00:34:33.529 --> 00:34:34.780
(SIGHS)

542
00:34:36.699 --> 00:34:38.450
I was ashamed.

543
00:34:39.243 --> 00:34:40.828
And I was scared.

544
00:34:42.496 --> 00:34:44.999
You take these things out
on the ones you love the most.

545
00:34:45.082 --> 00:34:46.584
for some reason.

546
00:34:52.673 --> 00:34:54.174
(SIGHS)

547
00:35:01.390 --> 00:35:03.517
You're blaming yourself. huh?

548
00:35:07.229 --> 00:35:09.189
Who else is there to blame?

549
00:35:11.859 --> 00:35:13.694
There is no one to blame at all.

550
00:35:14.570 --> 00:35:16.780
I wasn't supposed to be
in there by myself.

551
00:35:16.864 --> 00:35:18.449
Well. that is your reason.

552
00:35:18.532 --> 00:35:20.659
Rip's reason will be that

553
00:35:20.743 --> 00:35:23.829
he should have sold that horse sooner

554
00:35:23.912 --> 00:35:25.956
or he should have come back in.

555
00:35:27.875 --> 00:35:31.170
Lloyd is blaming himself for
a reason that I can't think of.

556
00:35:32.546 --> 00:35:34.798
But the reality is. honey...

557
00:35:36.258 --> 00:35:38.302
Colby made a choice.

558
00:35:39.345 --> 00:35:40.554
He saw you in trouble.

559
00:35:42.181 --> 00:35:43.807
And he chose to help you.

560
00:35:45.309 --> 00:35:47.394
And I'm sure glad that he did.

561
00:35:49.855 --> 00:35:51.440
I'm grateful.

562
00:35:53.067 --> 00:35:54.902
And you should be. too.

563
00:35:56.111 --> 00:35:58.197
Otherwise. he did it for nothing.

564
00:36:00.199 --> 00:36:03.035
So. you can honor his sacrifice.

565
00:36:04.495 --> 00:36:06.246
Or you can squander it.

566
00:36:07.581 --> 00:36:09.583
And that will be your fault.

567
00:36:16.924 --> 00:36:18.842
(SIGHS)

568
00:36:24.765 --> 00:36:26.100
You gonna stay here tonight?

569
00:36:28.060 --> 00:36:30.229
I-I don't know.

570
00:36:30.312 --> 00:36:32.439
Well. if I were you. I. uh.

571
00:36:33.232 --> 00:36:36.443
I wouldn't want to wrestle
with this by myself.

572
00:36:38.487 --> 00:36:40.823
I'd want to be with my family.

573
00:36:42.116 --> 00:36:43.659
I don't got a family.

574
00:36:46.787 --> 00:36:48.455
Sure you do.

575
00:36:51.125 --> 00:36:52.960
(DOOR OPENS)

576
00:36:53.836 --> 00:36:55.379
(DOOR CLOSES)

577
00:36:55.462 --> 00:36:57.589
(SERENE MUSIC)

578
00:37:19.653 --> 00:37:21.864
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

579
00:37:53.479 --> 00:37:55.564
I'm gonna light a fire.

580
00:37:58.192 --> 00:37:59.735
It's too warm for a fire.

581
00:37:59.818 --> 00:38:01.028
I know.

582
00:38:02.029 --> 00:38:03.947
But I like looking at 'em.

583
00:38:08.535 --> 00:38:10.454
A little...

584
00:38:10.537 --> 00:38:12.706
Boy Scout juice.

585
00:38:23.008 --> 00:38:24.885
Et voilà.

586
00:38:28.222 --> 00:38:29.848
Now. when you
throw your whiskey glass

587
00:38:29.932 --> 00:38:33.268
in the fire. you get a big fireball.

588
00:38:33.352 --> 00:38:35.854
You'll really feel like
you did something.

589
00:38:37.481 --> 00:38:40.400
Why would I throw my glass
in the fire. Beth?

590
00:38:42.402 --> 00:38:44.446
Well. baby.
you need to throw something.

591
00:38:44.530 --> 00:38:46.448
Hey. I'm not gonna watch you

592
00:38:46.532 --> 00:38:48.325
bottle this up all night.

593
00:38:48.408 --> 00:38:50.077
(LIQUID POURING)

594
00:38:51.411 --> 00:38:53.747
You want me to throw something?

595
00:39:06.385 --> 00:39:08.095
Feel good. huh?

596
00:39:23.694 --> 00:39:27.447
You know. when I find myself
in the position of therapist...

597
00:39:30.284 --> 00:39:32.452
this family's pretty fucked.

598
00:39:34.997 --> 00:39:36.582
So. what do you need?

599
00:39:38.125 --> 00:39:39.835
What do you need to...

600
00:39:41.295 --> 00:39:43.088
not feel this pain or this guilt.

601
00:39:43.171 --> 00:39:44.590
whatever it is you're feeling?

602
00:39:47.050 --> 00:39:50.971
All I ever need
is time and you. Beth.

603
00:39:56.727 --> 00:39:58.770
You know. if I started feeling guilty

604
00:39:58.854 --> 00:40:02.149
for all the...
the mistakes I've made...

605
00:40:05.193 --> 00:40:07.195
guilt is all I'd feel.

606
00:40:09.656 --> 00:40:11.241
Do I wish I would have gone myself?

607
00:40:11.325 --> 00:40:13.410
Hell yeah. I do. but...

608
00:40:13.493 --> 00:40:14.995
goddamn it. I didn't.

609
00:40:26.173 --> 00:40:28.216
It's a dangerous job.

610
00:40:30.677 --> 00:40:32.763
And one day it'll kill me. too.

611
00:40:38.185 --> 00:40:39.811
You know. this room...

612
00:40:40.896 --> 00:40:43.190
is the only one in the house I like.

613
00:40:46.985 --> 00:40:48.612
Yeah.

614
00:40:50.948 --> 00:40:52.866
Me too.

615
00:41:13.887 --> 00:41:16.556
You care to explain this to me?

616
00:41:19.017 --> 00:41:20.519
I do not.

617
00:41:22.896 --> 00:41:25.315
What I'm doing
isn't best for the ranch.

618
00:41:25.399 --> 00:41:27.317
It's what's best for you.

619
00:41:27.401 --> 00:41:28.694
For us.

620
00:41:37.369 --> 00:41:39.162
I'll be back tomorrow night.

621
00:41:39.246 --> 00:41:40.914
Promise?

622
00:41:41.581 --> 00:41:42.582
I swear.

623
00:41:42.666 --> 00:41:44.626
(PENSIVE MUSIC)

624
00:41:50.549 --> 00:41:52.175
I can see it now.

625
00:41:53.468 --> 00:41:55.137
I know what to do.

626
00:41:56.346 --> 00:41:57.764
Believe in me.

627
00:41:59.099 --> 00:42:00.809
(SCOFFS SOFTLY)

628
00:42:00.892 --> 00:42:03.103
I've always believed in you. Kayce.

629
00:42:05.105 --> 00:42:06.606
I love you.

630
00:42:07.941 --> 00:42:09.109
Come back to us.

631
00:42:10.610 --> 00:42:12.154
You have my word.

632
00:42:24.875 --> 00:42:27.127
(WIND SOFTLY WHISTLING)

633
00:42:45.645 --> 00:42:47.064
Morning.

634
00:42:47.147 --> 00:42:49.107
(BETH SIGHS)

635
00:42:49.191 --> 00:42:50.817
That it is.

636
00:42:51.693 --> 00:42:53.320
I mean. good morning.

637
00:42:56.490 --> 00:42:58.241
Well. that's fairly presumptuous

638
00:42:58.325 --> 00:43:01.036
based on the string of mornings
we've put together lately.

639
00:43:02.120 --> 00:43:03.413
You want breakfast?

640
00:43:05.207 --> 00:43:06.583
Already made it.

641
00:43:06.666 --> 00:43:10.170
Um. can you ask Kayce to join me
on the porch when he's done?

642
00:43:10.837 --> 00:43:12.089
He left.

643
00:43:13.548 --> 00:43:14.841
Left where?

644
00:43:15.509 --> 00:43:16.551
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

645
00:43:16.635 --> 00:43:17.761
(PARENTS CHEERING. CLAMORING)

646
00:43:17.844 --> 00:43:20.263
Come on. Ally. Don't let 'em out.

647
00:43:20.347 --> 00:43:21.932
Oh. pass it! Pass left!

648
00:43:22.015 --> 00:43:23.517
Shoot it!

649
00:43:23.600 --> 00:43:24.893
-(WHISTLE BLOWS)
(WHOOPS)

650
00:43:26.520 --> 00:43:29.314
There you go! Nice job. ladies.

651
00:43:29.397 --> 00:43:30.732
(CHEERING. APPLAUSE CONTINUING)

652
00:43:30.816 --> 00:43:33.110
Good job! Way to go!

653
00:43:33.193 --> 00:43:34.444
Good job. sport.

654
00:43:35.904 --> 00:43:37.114
All right. you did the right thing.

655
00:43:37.197 --> 00:43:38.448
When someone's
posted up in front of you.

656
00:43:38.532 --> 00:43:40.283
you pass to the open forward.

657
00:43:40.367 --> 00:43:41.493
But she got the goal.

658
00:43:41.576 --> 00:43:43.120
Yeah. but you got the win.

659
00:43:43.203 --> 00:43:45.122
Come on.

660
00:43:49.709 --> 00:43:51.086
Seat belt.

661
00:43:58.802 --> 00:44:00.512
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

662
00:44:01.805 --> 00:44:02.806
Drive.

663
00:44:03.515 --> 00:44:05.976
Start the car and drive
or you can clean up the mess.

664
00:44:13.733 --> 00:44:15.193
Where am I going?

665
00:44:15.277 --> 00:44:17.571
Just drive straight and
drive the fucking speed limit.

666
00:44:21.283 --> 00:44:22.409
You should be scared.

667
00:44:22.492 --> 00:44:24.202
You know what
your daddy does for a living?

668
00:44:26.913 --> 00:44:28.999
Do you know who I am?

669
00:44:29.082 --> 00:44:30.834
I do not.

670
00:44:30.917 --> 00:44:32.961
Get so cocky in the private
sector you forgot

671
00:44:33.044 --> 00:44:36.423
to build out immediate family
on a target. Grant?

672
00:44:36.506 --> 00:44:37.799
It's not the way you were trained.

673
00:44:37.883 --> 00:44:39.176
Listen. man. what we do.
it is strictly...

674
00:44:39.259 --> 00:44:41.428
I want you to listen.
I don't want you to talk.

675
00:44:41.511 --> 00:44:44.014
I am what you are.
You understand what I mean by that?

676
00:44:44.097 --> 00:44:45.432
Yeah. I understand what you mean.

677
00:44:45.515 --> 00:44:47.017
You got separation.
You can't be connected.

678
00:44:47.100 --> 00:44:48.685
Great. you saved me the trouble.

679
00:44:48.768 --> 00:44:50.061
But if you try to hedge your bets

680
00:44:50.145 --> 00:44:51.938
by getting distance with my family.

681
00:44:52.022 --> 00:44:54.065
I will paint yours
on the fucking wall.

682
00:44:55.275 --> 00:44:56.651
I should kill you in front of her

683
00:44:56.735 --> 00:44:58.361
for what you did to my father.

684
00:44:58.445 --> 00:45:00.655
but I'm gonna trade
my family for yours.

685
00:45:03.074 --> 00:45:05.035
You think you can't be touched?

686
00:45:05.118 --> 00:45:06.703
Look how easy this was for me.

687
00:45:06.786 --> 00:45:08.205
I have 12 years in the teams.

688
00:45:08.288 --> 00:45:09.956
Think about
how many friends I have.

689
00:45:10.040 --> 00:45:11.917
You don't want this fight.
You can't win it.

690
00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:13.460
We got enough separation.

691
00:45:13.543 --> 00:45:14.794
-We don't need anything else.
-Pull over.

692
00:45:20.884 --> 00:45:22.385
I have your DoD file.

693
00:45:22.469 --> 00:45:24.429
I know your address.

694
00:45:24.512 --> 00:45:25.931
I know where your parents live.

695
00:45:26.014 --> 00:45:28.850
I know where your wife works.
I know everything.

696
00:45:29.935 --> 00:45:32.437
You touched me. but I can
touch you whenever I want.

697
00:45:34.397 --> 00:45:37.025
It's bottled up.
You and me. we're good.

698
00:45:37.108 --> 00:45:39.069
We're so far from fucking good
you couldn't see it

699
00:45:39.152 --> 00:45:42.113
standing on your roof
at 2713 West Elm.

700
00:45:43.365 --> 00:45:44.699
If I were you. I'd move.

701
00:45:44.783 --> 00:45:45.951
'Cause I might
wake up tomorrow and decide

702
00:45:46.034 --> 00:45:48.495
we don't have a deal. You got me?

703
00:45:49.162 --> 00:45:50.163
No!

704
00:45:50.247 --> 00:45:52.040
Stop. please.

705
00:45:52.123 --> 00:45:54.251
Where I come from.
we call that counting coup.

706
00:45:54.334 --> 00:45:55.835
That means
I took a piece of your soul

707
00:45:55.919 --> 00:45:57.587
and I'm gonna keep it.

708
00:45:57.671 --> 00:46:00.340
And. yeah. you should cry.

709
00:46:00.423 --> 00:46:03.009
Have fun explaining this to your wife.

710
00:46:03.093 --> 00:46:05.136
When I get out. you take off.

711
00:46:05.220 --> 00:46:07.472
You look back. I kill you both.

712
00:46:30.161 --> 00:46:31.788
How'd it go?

713
00:46:32.872 --> 00:46:34.749
I think he understands.

714
00:46:34.833 --> 00:46:36.793
Did you count coup?

715
00:46:36.876 --> 00:46:38.545
I counted coup.

716
00:46:39.796 --> 00:46:41.047
Then he understands.

717
00:47:02.902 --> 00:47:04.904
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)
